a hello world for an android app that runs python/javascript scripts,

using SL4A and an embedded python interpreter ( for python script )
using Rhino ( for javascript )

GetPythonScript button -> fetch and run a python script from a web site
GetJavascript button -> fetch and run a javascript script from a web site

To write a script for the app go to http://83.212.115.57/cannon/ and write something like this to the textarea:

(Python example -> make a Toast message)

import android
droid = android.Android()
droid.makeToast("Hello happy android from python...")



(Javascript example -> write to android LogCat)

var log = android.util.Log;
log.i("HITAG","hello happy android from javascript");


